Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_tcic(25.10)                                            check_tcic(25.10)

Name
       check_tcic - Note: The fix_floorplan command can be used to fix the re-
       ported violations

Syntax
        check_tcic

       [-help]

       [<filename>]

       [-pre_opt]

       [-report_area]

       [-report_file <filename>]

       [-report_unplaced_block]

       [-include_all_rules ]

       [-selected_rules <rule_name>]

       Checks the floorplan constraints defined in tCIC files and reports vio-
       lations. These violations can be seen in the Violation Browser.

       Note:  The fix_floorplan command can be used to fix the reported viola-
       tions.

       Note: The check_tcic command honors the setFPlanMode -no_cut_row  para-
       meter  that  specifies if rows are not required to be cut before opera-
       tions. With  setFPlanMode  -no_cut_row  false  or  not  specified,  the
       check_tcic  command  will  work based on the current row shape. If rows
       are not cut before the check_tcic command  is  run,  with  setFPlanMode
       -no_cut_row true, the check_tcic command will work based on the cut row
       shape.  The actual row shape is not changed after these operations. You
       can still get the expected check result for row's rule without  running
       the cutRow before.

Parameters
       <filename>
              Specifies the name of tCIC file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each check_tcic parameter. For a detailed descrip-
              tion of the command and all of its parameters, use the man  com-
              mand:

              man check_tcic

       -include_all_rules
              Enables  the  tool  to  report the summary of violations for all
              rules.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pre_opt
              Enables pre-optimization.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -report_area
              Enables the  tool to report the object area data in summary.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -report_file <filename>
              Specifies the name of the file that saves the report summary.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -report_unplaced_block
              Enables the tool to show the number of unplaced macros  in  sum-
              mary.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -selected_rules <rule_name>
              Specifies that only the selected rules will be checked.

              Note: The -selected_rules parameter supports the variable format
              for specifying the rule list.

              For example, you can define a rule in the tCIC file and then use
              the check_tcic command to check the rule.

              set sanity_rules `A C'

              check_tcic RULE.tcl -selected_rules $sanity_rules

              Here, rule A and C will be checked

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              *

                The  following  command  checks  the  floorplan  based  on the
                RULE.tcl file that contains the user specified tCIC rules:

                check_tcic RULE.tcl

Related Information
              * fix_floorplan

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

